nodes.bodyText:
Following up on this comment, there is quite a lot to chew on in this method.
I wonder if we can avoid the check for 'lastGroup != null' with an early termination condition. The last group being null would seem to imply that something is empty. It's not quite clear to me what that thing would be, like, how would we get a null value here? I'm ultimately wondering if we can update the code in a way to moot this question and basically early terminate if we are going to have a null last group.
Perhaps something like this:
      if (!guaranteedGroups.isEmpty()) {
        final List<Unit> lastGroup = guaranteedGroups.peekLast();
        // if the last group isn't the right size, put those units in the remainder list
        if (lastGroup.size() != guaranteeHitGroupSize) {
          guaranteedGroups.removeLast();
          remainderUnits.addAll(lastGroup);
        }
        guaranteedHitGroups.addAll(guaranteedGroups);
      }

