nodes.bodyText:
The body of the if statement takes a bit more effort to understand IMHO then is strictly necessary largely because we are re-using a variable from the peek last that we already used to determine if there is a remainder.
From this:
        guaranteedGroups.removeLast();
        remainderUnits.addAll(lastGroup);

I think it would be a bit easier to make this transfer explicit and eliminate the need for the reader to remember what the lastGroup variable is (particularly after it has been used for a different purpose). Suggestion:
var groupWithRemainderUnits = guaranteedGroups.removeLast();
remainderUnits.addAll(groupWithRemainderUnits);

